      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NORMANS GIRL (3) finished fifth last start over 1720m at Melton, beaten 8 metres, after a good win at Kilmore the run prior. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run and rates a primary contender if she is at her best. ALPHA CRUCIS (2) settled in the leading division then found the lead only to be claimed in the straight and finish second last start over 2080m at this track, that run on the back of an unplaced effort at Charlton the run before. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Won't find this any harder and he can give this a mighty shake. ELLEEGANT LANE (7) is on the radar after her last-start fifth over 1690m at Kilmore eight days ago. Top-three prospects. STAR RULER NZ (1) is worth some thought after his last-start sixth over 1680m at Terang on March 27. In the mix from the low draw.",
